class Solution {
public:
    bool isUgly(int num) {
        if(num<=0){
            return false;
        }
        int remain=num;
        while(remain%2==0){
            remain/=2;
        }
        while(remain%3==0){
            remain/=3;
        }
        while(remain%5==0){
            remain/=5;
        }
        return remain==1;
    }
};
==========================================
263. Ugly Number
Write a program to check whether a given number is an ugly number.

Ugly numbers are positive numbers whose prime factors only include 2, 3, 5.

Example 1:

Input: 6
Output: true
Explanation: 6 = 2 Ã— 3
